HEADWORD: paddymelon
<hw>paddymelon</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Any of several small
reddish-brown wallabies of scrubby areas of Australia and New Guinea,
especially those belonging to the genus <gen>Thylogale</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pademelon.</syn>⟦br⟧
